üß† 2-bit 4-location RAM ‚Äì Digital Memory Design



This project involves the design and simulation of a 2-bit wide, 4-location Random Access Memory (RAM) using Verilog HDL. It is a compact memory model designed to demonstrate the working of digital memory blocks typically found in processor cache or embedded systems.

Each memory location stores a 2-bit value, and there are four such locations addressable via a 2-bit address input. The memory supports synchronous write (controlled by clock and write enable) and asynchronous read, enabling users to understand key concepts of memory timing and control.

This project serves as a foundational module for learning digital system design and is ideal for beginners working with FPGAs, memory modeling, or VLSI design.
